glosses: To replace with a new or fresh one; to refresh, to replenish.
To go over or to redo something, to repeat.
To revive an emotion or a thought that had been forgotten; to rekindle, to reawaken.

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish تازهلمك (tāzelemek, “to renew, to freshen up, to replenish”), from Ottoman Turkish تازه (tāze, “fresh, new, young and tender, raw, inexperienced”), from Persian تازه (tâze, “fresh, new”). By surface analysis, taze + -le + -mek.
